Friday Olokor, Abuja The Independent National Electoral Commission said it would on Monday, October 14, 2019, publish the register of voters and present same to all the political parties sponsoring candidates for the November 16 governorship elections in Bayelsa and Kogi states. A statement on Wednesday  by INEC National Commissioner and chairman of its Information and Voter Education Committee, Festus Okoye, said, “The events will take place at the commission’s offices in Yenagoa for Bayelsa State and Lokoja for Kogi State and will be presided over by the supervising national commissioners and assisted by the Resident Electoral Commissioners of the respective states. “From our records. a total of 45 political parties will take part in the governorship election in Bayelsa State while 23 will contest in Kogi State, being those who are sponsoring validly nominated candidates.” INEC appealed to all candidates to avoid comments capable of inciting violence and instilling fear during their campaigns. Copyright PUNCH.
